body_html:
Thanks a lot for your info.

I run into this issue when i perform the following command. (This command comes from Nvidia's official tutorial on using Tensorflow. http://www.nvidia.com/object/gpu-accelerated-applications-tensorflow-running-jobs.html.)

bazel-bin/inception/flowers_train --train_dir=$FLOWERS_DIR/train --data_dir=$FLOWERS_DIR/data --pretrained_model_checkpoint_path=$INCEPTION_DIR/inception-v3/model.ckpt-157585 --fine_tune=True --initial_learning_rate=0.001 -input_queue_memory_factor=1 --max_steps=500 --num_gpus 1 --batch_size=64

Therefore, I failed to use "python -m pdb script.py" to debug.

As its error msg indicated, "TypeError: Expected int32, got list containing Tensors of type '_Message' instead."

Does this msg provide any info useful? Look forward to your kindly support.:-)
